title: Don't look down! Massive bear hangs from side of Colorado home in attempt to make daring escape
description: A Colorado brown bear swung from the window of a house it had broken into for several minutes before deciding there was a better way out.

title: Neighbor of NYC financier accused of raping girl, 14, says child was often seen around his apartment
description: Michael Olson (pictured) was allegedly regularly seen with a young girl outside his Manhattan apartment long before his disturbing indictment over claims he drugged and raped a girl, 14.

title: Nationals' Bridget McKenzie 'aware of rumours' before David Van sexual assault allegations
description: Senator Van resigned from the Liberal Party a day before a committee was due to discuss allegations he inappropriately touched three women.

title: Rochedale State High School teacher, Bradley Flavel, pleads guilty after sexually assaulting girl
description: Bradley William Flavel, 31, plead guilty to two counts of indecent treatment of a child under the age of 16 and one count of carnal knowledge with a child under the age of 16 on Friday.

title: Registered sex offender Warren 'Wazza' Wright disowned by charities Beyond Blue and R U OK?
description: Two charities have denied having any links with a convicted child sex offender who is travelling from town to town in north west Victoria claiming to be raising money for mental health issues.

title: Masseuse caught with drugs after leaving Andrew O'Keefe's house is fined
description: Mitchell Rees Sturt, 52, was stopped by officers moments after exiting Andrew O'Keefe's Vaucluse home in Sydney's eastern suburbs during the early hours of November 24.

title: Beloved star of Discovery Channel's Flying Wild Alaska dies in small plane crash above state
description: Bush pilot Jim Tweto, the star of Discovery Channel's 'Flying Wild Alaska', was killed along with a hunting and fishing guide from Idaho when their small plane crashed shortly after takeoff Friday.

title: Wall Street should brace for a big collapse after recent rally, warns Bank of America analyst
description: Bank of America Chief Investment Strategist Michael Hartnett doesn't believe it's the start of a 'brand, new shiny bull market' but that stocks are headed for 'big rally before big collapse.'

title: NSW police dog bites into teenager's arm after boy fled cops during South Kempsey arrest
description: Police visited a house on Reginald Ward Street in South Kempsey, north of Port Macquarie, just before 1pm on Thursday.

title: Antony Blinken in Beijing: Secretary of State lands in China on diplomatic mission
description: Blinken was to begin two days of talks with senior Chinese officials in the afternoon. He is the highest-level American official to visit China since President Joe Biden took office.

title: Bruce Highway crash: Car flips after being hit by truck on main road into Brisbane
description: Video shared by Dashcam Owners Australia this week stated said the collision occurred on the Bruce Highway coming into Brisbane.

title: Kevin Costner's wife looks unbothered as she leaves $145million home she refuses to vacate
description: Kevin Costner's estranged wife Christine Baumgartner was spotted Saturday, looking crabby as she ran errands near her family home in Carpinteria, California.

title: Prince William pledges to 'end homelessness' and plans to build social housing on Duchy of Cornwall
description: William spoke in his first interview since becoming the Prince of Wales, and used it to explain that he is determined to 'make a difference... that doesn't set people up that are homeless for another fall'.

title: Brittany Higgins and David Sharaz political masterplan before meeting The Project's Lisa Wilkinson
description: Leaked audio reveals Brittany Higgins and partner David Sharaz had schemed to ensure the explosive allegations would cause the biggest uproar in Canberra before the next federal election.

title: Keir Starmer's chief of staff Sue Gray 'could have been sacked from civil service' after Labour move
description: Sue Gray (pictured), the top civil servant poached by Sir Keir Starmer to be his new chief of staff did breach Whitehall impartiality rules, an official Cabinet Office inquiry said, it was reported last night.

title: Mystery over the condition of Kyiv's 'incredibly ruthless' spy chief
description: Major-General Kyrylo Budanov, 37, was last seen in early June in a flashy promotional video from the Ukrainian military about their counter-offensive, titled Plans Love Silence.

title: Ex-Oasis manager Alan McGee denies two allegations of rape as Metropolitan Police launch probe
description: Alan McGee, 62, has been accused of two separate rapes in Southwark and Kensington and Chelsea in London, it was revealed last night.

title: Is Meghan about to become the mega-bucks Duchess of Dior?
description: CAROLINE GRAHAM: The Duchess has been immersed in meetings since signing with Emanuel, as Netflix conducts an 'ongoing review' of £80 million deal.

title: SNP fraud detectives probe 'cash in envelopes' claims
description: Allegations made by a whistleblower state that senior party figures received tens of thousands of pounds from a Scottish businessman related to a prominent nationalist politician.

title: It's click-and-collect... at Glastonbury! Festivalgoers can order shopping to the campsite
description: Last year, revellers complained about vendors' 'rip-off' prices, with pints of beer costing from £6 and a slice of Margherita pizza priced at £7.

title: Woman pressured into breast removal at 13 under 'erroneous belief' she was transgender: lawsuit
description: Kayla Lovdahl (pictured) slammed the medical industry that pushed her to have a double mastectomy aged just 13 as 'ideological and profit-driven medical abuse' in a bombshell new lawsuit.

title: Motorcyclist dies after crashing bike into St Nicholas Anglican Church in Goulburn
description: Emergency services were called to St Nicholas Anglican Church on Kinghorne St in Goulburn after the man was found by a passer-by just before 8.30pm.

title: Car smashed into Sydney Guildford front yard after high-speed police chase
description: Youseff Rima, 37, allegedly rolled his Hyundai Tucson SUV after reaching speeds of up to 140km/h in Guildford, western Sydney, at 11pm on Friday.
